================================================================
PHASE 3A — CANONICAL CUSTOMER-FACING COPY (ALL SERVICES)
STATUS: FINAL FREEZE — MATRIX & ARCHITECTURE COMPLIANT
================================================================

GLOBAL PHASE 3A RULES (LOCKED)
- One question per assistant turn
- One neutral bridge max (clean answers only)
- No persuasion, no benefit framing
- No pricing in Phase 3A
- Fallback / nudge only once per qualifier
- If fallback ignored → set qualifier = UNKNOWN → proceed
- Brand / warranty acknowledged but deferred
- Comparison captured, not neutralised
================================================================


========================================================
SERVICE: PPF
========================================================

Q1 — COVERAGE INTENT

Assistant:
Just so I guide you correctly and don’t over- or under-quote,
are you thinking full protection, front protection, or still deciding?

CLEAN ANSWERS:
Customer: Full / Front / Not sure

Assistant (bridge + Q2):
That helps narrow the direction.
How you use the car affects which option makes sense.
Is your driving mostly highways and travel, or mostly city use?

PRICE INTERRUPTION:
Customer: How much? / Price?

Assistant (fallback):
I’ll give you the price — this just helps me make it accurate.
Are you thinking full protection, front protection, or still deciding?

(If repeated → Coverage = UNKNOWN)

BRAND / WARRANTY:
Customer: Is it XPEL? / Warranty?

Assistant:
We can get into brands and warranty shortly — first I want to be sure about the direction.
Are you thinking full protection, front protection, or still deciding?

COMPARISON:
Customer: Another place is cheaper.

Assistant:
I understand comparisons matter — let’s make sure we’re comparing the right scope first.
Are you thinking full protection, front protection, or still deciding?


Q2 — USAGE / RISK FRAMING

Assistant:
How you use the car affects which option makes sense.
Is your driving mostly highways and travel, or mostly city use?

CLEAN ANSWERS:
Customer: Highway / City / Mixed

Assistant (if Q3 triggered):
That helps clarify the priorities.
When you’re comparing options, is your focus mainly on coverage, quality, or price?

WHY QUESTION:
Customer: Why does that matter?

Assistant:
Because highway and city use affect where wear and exposure usually happen.
Is your driving more highway-focused or city-focused?

PRICE INTERRUPTION:
Customer: Just give the price.

Assistant (fallback):
I’ll price it right after this — usage helps avoid recommending the wrong option.
Is your driving more highway or city use?

(If repeated → Usage = UNKNOWN)


Q3 — COMPARISON FOCUS (CONDITIONAL)

Assistant:
That makes sense.
When you’re comparing, is your focus mainly on coverage, quality, or price?

CLEAN ANSWERS:
Customer: Price / Quality / Coverage / All

Assistant (closure):
That helps frame the next step.

→ Phase 3A ends


